It will be a lot of errors if scan all the files in k/k when we add a new rule. We could have something like this:

```go
package main

import (
	"bufio"
	"fmt"
	"io"
	"os"
)

func main() {
	reader := bufio.NewReader(os.Stdin)

	files := []string{}
	for {
		file, err := reader.ReadString('\n')
		if err != nil {
			if err == io.EOF {
				break
			}

			panic(err)
		}

		files = append(files, file)
	}

	fmt.Println(files)
}

```

And update the script in the shell as [1] which could verify the changes with master

